Class MoveCommand

java.lang.Object
  lps.pr2.commands.Command
      lps.pr2.commands.MoveCommand
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Cloneable
public class MoveCommand
extends Command

The Movement command. It parses the input in order to move the player in a given direction. This direction is stored in order to execute and undo this command.

See Also:

parse

public boolean parse(java.lang.String line)
Parses a (GO | MOVE) (NORTH| N | SOUTH | S | WEST | W | EAST | E) command

Specified by:
parse in class Command
Parameters:
line - A string with the information for configuring the command
Returns:
  • False, if this command does not know how to parse the line or if the line contains mistakes and the command cannot be configured correctly.
  • True, otherwise. In this case, the command is correctly configured and ready to be executed
